data.description: Compensating for overlaps in wall lines will reduce the flow rate of some of the walls. If this flow rate gets below the value of the Minimum Wall Flow setting, a travel move is made instead of the wall line. If this setting is enabled, the filament will be retracted during that travel move.
data.hints: - Enabling this setting will increase print time and wear on the filament, but could improve the visual quality of your walls.
